      "/uploads/tours/annapurna-base-camp-trek-12-nights-13-days/tour_1766482629935.webp"
    ],
    "highlights": [
      "Warm welcome and cultural introduction in Kathmandu, the capital of Nepal",
      "Scenic drive from Kathmandu to Pokhara, Nepal\u2019s most beautiful lakeside city",
      "Classic trekking route via Nayapul, Tikhedhunga, Ghorepani, Tadapani, and Chhomrong",
      "Sunrise hike to Poon Hill (3,210 m) with spectacular panoramic views of Annapurna and Dhaulagiri ranges",
      "Walk through lush rhododendron forests, terraced farmland, and traditional Gurung villages",
      "Trek through the scenic Modi Khola valley toward the heart of the Annapurna Sanctuary",
      "Overnight at Machhapuchhre Base Camp (MBC) surrounded by towering Himalayan peaks",
      "Reach the breathtaking Annapurna Base Camp (4,230 m), encircled by Annapurna I, Hiunchuli, and Machhapuchhre",
      "Descend through bamboo forests to Jhinu, famous for its natural hot springs",
      "Relaxing stay and sightseeing tour in Pokhara, including lakes, caves, and viewpoints",
      "A perfect blend of mountain adventure, culture, and natural beauty in one unforgettable journey"
    ],
    "inclusions": [
      "Personalized airport meet & greet with private pick-up and drop-off services in Kathmandu",
      "Hotel accommodation premium hotels in Kathmandu and Pokhara with daily breakfast",
      "All meals during the trekking period, freshly prepared with hygienic standards (choice of local & international menus)",
      "Best available mountain lodges/guesthouses along the trekking route for maximum comfort",
      "All required trekking permits and entrance fees, including TIMS Card and Annapurna Conservation Area Permit (ACAP)",
      "Highly experienced, government-licensed English-speaking trekking guide",
      "Dedicated porter service (1 porter for every 2 trekkers) to ensure a light and comfortable trek",
      "Comprehensive staff support, including guide and porter insurance, salaries, meals, accommodation, equipment, and transportation",
      "Private and comfortable ground transportation (air-conditioned vehicles / tourist deluxe buses as per route)",
      "Professional trek management and safety monitoring throughout the journey",
      "Emergency rescue coordination and evacuation assistance (covered by traveler\u2019s insurance)",
      "First-aid medical kit and oxygen support carried by the trekking guide",
      "Welcome and farewell fine-dining experiences in Kathmandu at a premium Nepali restaurant with cultural ambiance",
      "Porter-handled luggage allowance to enhance trekking comfort",
      "24/7 local assistance and on-ground support team",
      "All government taxes, service charges, and administrative fees"
    ],
