  {
    "id": 308,
    "slug": "everest-base-camp-trek-13n-14d",
    "title": "Everest Base Camp Trek - 13 Nights 14 Days",
    "category": "Trekking",
    "description": "Mount Everest (8848m) is the highest mountain the world towering above 8848 meters from sea level. Mount Everest also the most awaiting peaks in the world that people dream to conquer it. Obviously, there is no other place in the world more spectacular than Mount Everest. Trekking Experts designed this exclusive Everest Base Camp Trek to bring you closer to the world highest peak Mount Everest. \n\nEverest Base Camp Trek is beautiful and most popular trek in Nepal where thousands of people trek every year to the base camp of Mount Everest. Mount Everest is situated in Everest National Park (locally Sagarmatha National Park) of Nepal. Trekking in the Everest region offers you scenic mountain views, alpine vegetations and animals while you\u2019re trek and will get opportunities experience the life of world famous climbers; Sherpa people. The trek offers the opportunities to see the ranges of mountain ranges, Sagarmatha National Park, the world heritage site, the life style of the Sherpa people, Himalayan flora and fauna and will also get an opportunity to embark on an epic journey that our mountain legends Sir Edmund Hillary and Tenzing Norgay Sherpa set off in 1953. You will witness the highest altitude hotel in the world, The Everest Hotel, highest altitude airport Lukla airport also known as Tenzing Hillary Airport and high altitude places where people still live\n",
    "location": "Nepal",
    "price": 0,
    "duration": "14 days",
    "group_size": "2-12 people",
    "difficulty": "Challenging",
    "rating": 4.9,
    "reviews": 287,
    "best_time": "March-May, September-November",
    "featured": true,
    "listed": true,
    "image": "/uploads/tours/everest-base-camp-trek-13n-14d/tour_1766478467946.jpg",
    "gallery": [
      "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1605640840605-14ac1855827b?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D",
      "/uploads/tours/everest-base-camp-trek-13n-14d/tour_1766478483298.webp",
      "/uploads/tours/everest-base-camp-trek-13n-14d/tour_1766478483315.jpg",
      "/uploads/tours/everest-base-camp-trek-13n-14d/tour_1766478483341.jpg",
      "/uploads/tours/everest-base-camp-trek-13n-14d/tour_1766478483400.jpg",
      "/uploads/tours/everest-base-camp-trek-13n-14d/tour_1766478483487.jpg"
    ],
    "highlights": [
      "Arrival and sightseeing base in Kathmandu, the cultural heart of Nepal",
      "Scenic mountain flight to Lukla, one of the world\u2019s most thrilling airports",
      "Trek through classic Sherpa villages: Phakding, Namche Bazaar, Tengboche, Dingboche, Lobuche",
      "Acclimatization hikes to Hotel Everest View and Nangkartsang Peak",
      "Visit the famous Tengboche Monastery with stunning Himalayan backdrops",
      "Reach the legendary Everest Base Camp (5,364 m) \u2013 a lifetime achievement",
      "Sunrise hike to Kala Patthar (5,555 m) for panoramic views of Mt. Everest, Lhotse, Nuptse & Khumbu Glacier",
      "Walk alongside the mighty Khumbu Glacier and Icefall",
      "Experience authentic Sherpa culture, traditions, and hospitality",
      "Fully guided trek with gradual acclimatization for safety and comfort"
    ],
    "inclusions": [
      "Airport transfers (arrival & departure) in Kathmandu",
      "Hotel accommodation in Kathmandu on twin-sharing basis with breakfast",
      "Domestic flights: Kathmandu \u2013 Lukla \u2013 Kathmandu (as per operation)",
      "All trekking accommodation in guesthouses/teahouses during the trek",
      "Three meals per day during the trek (breakfast, lunch, and dinner)",
      "Licensed, experienced English-speaking trekking guide",
      "Porter service (1 porter for every 2 trekkers) with insurance",
      "Sagarmatha National Park Permit and Khumbu Pasang Lhamu Rural Municipality Permit",
      "Guide and porter salary, meals, accommodation, insurance, and equipment",
      "First aid medical kit carried by the guide",
      "All applicable government taxes and service charges"
    ],
    "exclusions": [
      "International airfare",
      "Nepal entry visa fee",
      "Travel and medical insurance (must include high-altitude trekking & helicopter evacuation)",
      "Personal trekking equipment (sleeping bag, down jacket, trekking poles, etc.)",
      "Extra porter beyond the included arrangement",
      "Beverages (alcoholic drinks, bottled water, soft drinks, tea/coffee during the trek)",
      "Hot showers, Wi-Fi, battery charging during the trek",
      "Tips for guide and porter (highly appreciated but not mandatory)",
      "Costs due to flight delays/cancellations caused by weather or other unforeseen circumstances",
      "Helicopter rescue/evacuation costs (covered by insurance)",
      "Any expenses not mentioned in the \u201cTour Inclusions\u201d section"
    ],
    "activities": [
      {
        "name": "High Altitude Trekking",
        "description": "Trek through diverse landscapes from subtropical forests to alpine terrain"
      },
      {
        "name": "Cultural Immersion",
        "description": "Experience Sherpa culture and visit Buddhist monasteries"
      },
      {
        "name": "Mountain Photography",
        "description": "Capture stunning views of world's highest peaks"
      },
      {
        "name": "Wildlife Viewing",
        "description": "Spot Himalayan wildlife in Sagarmatha National Park"
      }
    ],
    "itinerary": [
      {
        "day": 1,
        "title": "Arrival in Kathmandu (1,400 m)",
        "description": "Upon arrival at Tribhuvan International Airport, you will be warmly welcomed and transferred to a hotel in Kathmandu. After check-in, enjoy time to relax from your journey or explore the hotel\u2019s facilities. This day allows you to adjust to Nepal\u2019s atmosphere while enjoying refined comfort before heading into the Himalayas.",
        "accommodation": "3-Star luxury hotel in Kathmandu",
        "meals": "Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 2,
        "title": "Fly to Lukla & Trek to Phakding (2,610 m)",
        "description": "After an early breakfast, Transfer to the domestic airport of Kathmandu, you take a 45 minute spectacular flight that takes you to the airstrip at Lukla offering breathtaking aerial views of Himalayan peaks and deep valleys. Upon landing, begin your gentle trek toward Phakding, following the Dudh Koshi River through charming Sherpa villages, prayer wheels, and suspension bridges. The short trek allows your body to adapt gradually while enjoying pristine mountain scenery. Arrive at your luxury lodge and relax with warm hospitality and freshly prepared meals.\nTrek:3\u20134 hours",
        "accommodation": "Lodge",
        "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 3,
        "title": "Trek to Namche Bazaar (3,440 m)",
        "description": "Today\u2019s trek takes you deeper into the Khumbu region. Cross several iconic suspension bridges, including the famous Hillary Bridge, while enjoying views of snow-capped peaks. Enter Sagarmatha National Park and ascend gradually through pine forests. As you approach Namche Bazaar, catch your first glimpse of Mount Everest on a clear day. Namche, the Sherpa capital, offers bakeries, caf\u00e9s, and stunning viewpoints. Relax in a premium lodge with heated rooms and modern comforts.\nTrek:5\u20136 hours",
        "accommodation": "Lodge",
        "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 4,
        "title": "Acclimatization Day in Namche Bazaar",
        "description": "This important acclimatization day helps your body adapt to altitude while maintaining comfort. We need to acclimatize to be adapted at the high altitude that prevents acute mountain sickness. After the breakfast, visit around the Namche Bazaar, Khunde and Khumjung. The fabulous views of Mt. Everest (8848m), Tawoche (6542m), Thamserku (6808m), Kantega, Ama Dablam (6856m), Nuptse (7896m) and Lhotse (8511m) are the amazingly seen during the trip. Then back to Namche.",
        "accommodation": "Lodge",
        "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 5,
        "title": "Trek to Tengboche (3,860 m)",
        "description": "After breakfast, trek along a beautiful trail with breathtaking Himalayan panoramas. Descend to cross the Dudh Koshi River, then ascend gradually through rhododendron forests toward Tengboche. Visit the famous Tengboche Monastery, the spiritual center of the Khumbu region, set against a dramatic mountain backdrop. The peaceful atmosphere and chanting monks create a memorable cultural experience. Spend the evening relaxing in a premium lodge with stunning mountain views.\nTrek:5\u20136 hours",
        "accommodation": "Lodge",
        "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 6,
        "title": "Trek to Dingboche (4,410 m)",
        "description": "Continue your journey through traditional Sherpa villages such as Pangboche, passing ancient mani walls and stone houses. The landscape becomes more alpine as you gain altitude, with expansive views of Ama Dablam and surrounding peaks. The trail is gradual, allowing for comfortable acclimatization. Arrive at Dingboche, a beautiful village set in a wide valley, and enjoy the best available lodge with warm dining areas and attentive service.\nTrek: 5\u20136 hours",
        "accommodation": "Lodge",
        "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 7,
        "title": "Acclimatization Day at Dingboche",
        "description": "Today is dedicated to acclimatization and exploration. Take a guided hike to Nangkartsang Peak (5,083 m) for spectacular views of Makalu, Lhotse, and the Imja Valley. The climb is steady and rewarding, helping your body adapt safely to higher altitudes. Return to Dingboche for a relaxed afternoon with hot drinks, rest, and mountain views. This day is essential for ensuring comfort and success at Everest Base Camp.",
        "accommodation": "Lodge",
        "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 8,
        "title": "Trek to Lobuche (4,950 m)",
        "description": "The trail follows the edge of the Khumbu Glacier, offering dramatic views of ice formations and towering peaks. Pass the climbers\u2019 memorials at Thukla, honoring mountaineers who attempted Everest. The terrain becomes more rugged, but the pace remains comfortable under expert guidance. Arrive at Lobuche and settle into the best available lodge, enjoying warm meals and a peaceful evening surrounded by high Himalayan landscapes.\nTrek: 5\u20136 hours",
        "accommodation": "Lodge",
        "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 9,
        "title": "Trek to Everest Base Camp (5,364 m) & Gorak Shep (5,190 m)",
        "description": "This is the highlight of your journey. Trek to Gorak Shep, then continue to the legendary Everest Base Camp, walking alongside the Khumbu Glacier. Stand at the foot of the world\u2019s highest mountain and celebrate this lifetime achievement. After photos and exploration, return to Gorak Shep. Despite the altitude, luxury-level care ensures comfort and safety throughout the day.\nTrek: 8\u20139 hours",
        "accommodation": "Lodge",
        "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 10,
        "title": "Hike to Kalapathar (5545m), and back to Pheriche (4240m).",
        "description": "Early in the morning, we climb to the Kala Patthar and enjoy the golden sunrise views over the 8000 meter peaks. Kalapatthar is also a good viewpoint of the snowy peaks in the Everest region and its surroundings soak in. Then, we trek down to Gorakshep, have breakfast and trek down further towards Pheriche. Enjoy the success of Everest base camp and Kalapatthar.\nTrek: 7-8 hours",
        "accommodation": "Lodge",
        "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 11,
        "title": "Trek down to Namche (3440m).",
        "description": "We have an easy trekking day. After the breakfast, we begin to trek down from Pheriche to No rush today to descend from Pheriche to Namche Bazaar. We walk at our own pace, enjoying our descending and the animal activities. Walking through the rhododendron forest and along the Imja Khola, we gradually reach to our destination.\nTrek: 5-6 hours",
        "accommodation": "Lodge",
        "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 12,
        "title": "Namche to Lukla. ",
        "description": "Today, we begin to trek crossing the suspension bridges and walking through the gentle trail. This is also a last trekking day in the Everest region. After we arrive in Lukla, we have some wonderful moments in the evening. We enjoy the beautiful evening on the mountain.\nTrek: 5-6 hours",
        "accommodation": "Lodge",
        "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 13,
        "title": "Lukla - Fly back to Kathmandu.",
        "description": "The last moment in the mountain, we fly back to Kathmandu with the fascinating views of the Himalayan peaks. From the airport, we transfer you to the hotel. You have free time for shopping and refreshing the whole day. Or we can enjoy the dinner in the evening.",
        "accommodation": "3-Star luxury hotel in Kathmandu",
        "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 14,
        "title": "Kathmandu departure.",
        "description": "Concluding the Everest base camp trekking, our company representative drops you at the airport for the final departure.",
        "accommodation": "N/A",
        "meals": "Breakfast"
      }
    ],
