    ],
    "activities": [
      {
        "name": "Cultural Tours",
        "description": "Visit UNESCO World Heritage sites and ancient temples"
      },
      {
        "name": "Wildlife Safari",
        "description": "Jungle safari in Chitwan National Park"
      },
      {
        "name": "Scenic Drives",
        "description": "Beautiful mountain and valley views"
      }
    ],
    "itinerary": [
      {
        "day": 1,
        "title": "Gorakhpur \u2013 Drive to Lumbini (100 km | 3\u20134 hrs)",
        "description": "Upon arrival at Gorakhpur, you will be warmly welcomed and driven across the scenic Indo-Nepal border toward Lumbini, the sacred birthplace of Lord Buddha. Enjoy countryside views during the comfortable drive. On arrival in Lumbini, transfer to your hotel and complete the check-in process. The rest of the day is free to relax or explore the peaceful surroundings at your own pace. Absorb the spiritual ambiance of this UNESCO World Heritage Site. Overnight stay at the hotel in Lumbini.",
        "accommodation": "3- Star Hotel",
        "meals": "N/A"
      },
      {
        "day": 2,
        "title": "Lumbini Sightseeing \u2013 Drive to Pokhara (180 km | 8\u20139 hrs)",
        "description": "After breakfast, begin guided sightseeing in Lumbini, visiting the revered Mayadevi Temple, the historic Ashoka Pillar, and the tranquil Sacred Pond. These landmarks reflect deep spiritual and historical significance. Later, embark on a scenic drive to Pokhara, passing rivers, hills, and charming villages along the way. The journey offers beautiful natural landscapes of Nepal\u2019s mid-hills. Arrive in Pokhara by evening and check in to your hotel. Overnight stay in Pokhara.",
        "accommodation": "3- Star Hotel",
        "meals": "Breakfast"
      },
      {
        "day": 3,
        "title": "Pokhara Sightseeing",
        "description": "After breakfast, explore the highlights of Pokhara, a city blessed with natural beauty. Visit Bindabasini Temple, followed by the dramatic Devi\u2019s Waterfall and the mystical Gupteshwor Cave. Continue to the impressive Seti River Gorge, carved deep into limestone rock. Later, enjoy a relaxing one-hour boat ride on Phewa Lake, visiting the island-based Tal Barahi Temple. The day combines spirituality, adventure, and serenity. Return to the hotel for overnight stay in Pokhara.",
        "accommodation": "3- Star Hotel",
        "meals": "Breakfast"
      },
      {
        "day": 4,
        "title": "Pokhara \u2013 Drive to Kathmandu via Manakamana (210 km | 8\u20139 hrs)",
        "description": "Early morning after breakfast, drive toward Kathmandu through winding mountain highways and river valleys. En route, stop at Manakamana Temple, reached by cable car, where devotees believe wishes are fulfilled. Enjoy panoramic views of hills and rivers from the top. After darshan, continue your journey to Kathmandu, Nepal\u2019s vibrant capital city. On arrival, transfer to your hotel and relax after a long yet scenic drive. Overnight stay at a hotel in Kathmandu.",
        "accommodation": "3- Star Hotel",
        "meals": "Breakfast"
      },
      {
        "day": 5,
        "title": "Kathmandu City Sightseeing",
        "description": "After breakfast, enjoy a full-day guided tour of Kathmandu\u2019s cultural and spiritual landmarks. Visit the sacred Pashupatinath Temple, one of the holiest Hindu shrines. Continue to Budhanilkantha (Sleeping Vishnu), followed by Swayambhunath Stupa (Monkey Temple) offering panoramic city views. Explore Kathmandu Durbar Square, home to ancient palaces and the Living Goddess Kumari. This day showcases Nepal\u2019s rich heritage, art, and architecture. Return to the hotel for overnight stay in Kathmandu.",
        "accommodation": "3- Star Hotel",
        "meals": "Breakfast"
      },
      {
        "day": 6,
        "title": "Kathmandu \u2013 Drive to Chitwan (155 km | 6\u20137 hrs)",
        "description": "After breakfast, drive south toward Chitwan, passing scenic riverbanks and lush countryside. Upon arrival, transfer to your jungle resort and enjoy lunch. In the afternoon, embark on an exciting jeep safari inside Chitwan National Park, home to rhinos, deer, crocodiles, and diverse birdlife. In the evening, experience a traditional Tharu cultural dance show, offering insight into local tribal heritage. Relax at the resort after an adventurous day. Overnight stay in Chitwan.",
        "accommodation": "3- Star Hotel",
        "meals": "Breakfast"
      },
      {
        "day": 7,
        "title": "Chitwan \u2013 Drive to Gorakhpur (220 km | 8\u20139 hrs)",
        "description": "After breakfast, check out from the hotel and begin your return drive to Gorakhpur for final departure. Enjoy the changing landscapes as you travel through southern Nepal toward the border. This marks the end of a memorable journey filled with spirituality, culture, nature, and wildlife experiences across Nepal. Arrive at Gorakhpur with wonderful memories and smooth onward connections.",
        "accommodation": "N/A",
        "meals": "Breakfast"
      }
    ],
