      "Extra accommodation or meals due to early arrival or late departure",
      "Any costs arising from unforeseen circumstances (weather, landslides, flight delays)"
    ],
    "activities": [],
    "itinerary": [
      {
        "day": 1,
        "title": "Arrival in Kathmandu (1,400m)",
        "description": "Upon arrival at Tribhuvan International Airport, our representative will warmly welcome you and transfer you to your hotel. After check-in, you can relax or explore nearby streets filled with cafes, shops, and cultural landmarks. ",
        "accommodation": "3-Star Hotel",
        "meals": "N/A"
      },
      {
        "day": 2,
        "title": "Drive from Kathmandu to Dhunche (1,960m)",
        "description": "After breakfast, you\u2019ll drive to Dhunche, the gateway to Langtang National Park. The scenic journey passes through terraced farmlands, forests, rivers, and rural settlements along the Trishuli River. Upon arrival, explore the village and interact with local Tamang people.\n\nDrive Duration: 5\u20136 hours",
        "accommodation": "Tea House",
        "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 3,
        "title": "Trek from Dhunche to Chandanbari (Sing Gompa) \u2013 3,330m",
        "description": "Today\u2019s trek begins with a gradual ascent through pine forests and scenic trails. Passing through Ghatte Khola and Deurali, you\u2019ll enjoy peaceful surroundings and fresh mountain air. Chandanbari, also known as Sing Gompa, is famous for its monastery and yak cheese factory.\n\nTrek Duration: 5\u20136 hours",
        "accommodation": "Tea House",
        "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 4,
        "title": "Trek from Chandanbari to Gosaikunda (4,380m)",
        "description": "This is the most rewarding day of the trek. The trail ascends through rugged terrain with breathtaking views of Himalayan peaks. Along the way, you\u2019ll pass Cholangpati, Lauribina, and the sacred Bhairav Kunda and Saraswati Kunda before reaching Gosaikunda Lake. Spend time exploring the surrounding lakes and soaking in the spiritual atmosphere.\n\nTrek Duration: 5\u20136 hours",
        "accommodation": "Tea House",
        "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 5,
        "title": "Trek from Gosaikunda to Dhunche",
        "description": "After sunrise views over Gosaikunda, you\u2019ll begin your descent back to Dhunche via Lauribina and Chandanbari. The downhill trek offers a different perspective of the landscapes and increases chances of spotting wildlife such as Himalayan birds and, if lucky, the rare red panda.\n\nTrek Duration: 7\u20138 hours",
        "accommodation": "Tea House",
        "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch & Dinner"
      },
      {
        "day": 6,
        "title": "Drive from Dhunche to Kathmandu",
        "description": "Following breakfast, you\u2019ll drive back to Kathmandu, enjoying scenic views of hills, rivers, and countryside along the way. Upon arrival, check in to your hotel and enjoy a free evening for shopping or relaxation.\n\nDrive Duration: 5\u20136 hours",
        "accommodation": "3-Star Hotel",
        "meals": "Breakfast"
      },
      {
        "day": 7,
        "title": "Final Departure",
        "description": "Our team will transfer you to the airport for your onward journey. If you wish to extend your stay or add other tours, we\u2019ll be happy to arrange it for you.",
        "accommodation": "N/A",
        "meals": "Breakfast"
      }
    ],
